public class SmsCoreTest
extends org.sakaiproject.sms.hibernate.util.AbstractBaseTestCase

This test also send messages to the smpp simulator but it check the specific statuses of sent messages. It also test the retrieval of the next sms task from the SMS_TASK table.

Method Detail

testProcessNextTask

public void testProcessNextTask()
In this test the ProcessNextTask method is tested. 4 smsTasks are created with different sending times and statuses. The ProcessNextTask method must pick up the oldest SmsTask with an (pending/incomplete/reply) status. The test succeeds if the Smstasks are returned in the proper order and the correct amount of delivery reports were received. NOTE: Make sure that the SMS_TASK table is empty before running this test, else it will fail.

testProcessTaskFail

public void testProcessTaskFail()
In this test the smsc (gateway) is not bound (disconnected). The task is executed 5 times to simulate the scheduler retrying and eventually failing.

testTimeoutAndMessageStatusUpdate

public void testTimeoutAndMessageStatusUpdate()
In this test the updating of smsStatuses is tested. First a new task is created and populated with smsMessages.The total number of pending messages must equal 0 at the end.The total sent messages must equal the total messages on the task.Secondly a new task is created and the delivery report lister is switched off. After 1 min the core service must mark all the messages on the task as timedout.The test is successful if a timedout message is found.
